Given an integer array, determine whether it follows a Fibonacci-like sequence.
If the array follows a Fibonacci sequence, the method should return 1; otherwise, return 0.
Based on the method's return value, print whether it is a Fibonacci series or not.


Solution:

class Main {

    static int isFab(int[] arr) {

        if (arr.length < 3) return 0;

        for (int i = 2; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] != arr[i - 1] + arr[i - 2]) {
                return 0;
            }
        }
        return 1;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 5, 8}; 

        int result = isFab(arr);

        if (result == 1) {
            System.out.println("fab series");
        } else {
            System.out.println("non fab series");
        }
    }
}

O/P:

fab series
